================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

The kickstart, workflow, and findings in this repository build an ISO out of
packages and reference files from other projects. Each keeps its own
license. Nothing from these projects is vendored into this repository
except the handful of icon, logo, and reference files noted below.

Azure Linux
    Packages and repo metadata come from https://github.com/microsoft/azurelinux,
    MIT licensed. Every individual package pulled from Azure Linux's repos
    carries its own upstream license, same as any Linux distro. The five
    files under reference/azl-installer/ (azl-install.ks,
    azl-install-encrypted.ks, post-install.sh, post-bootloader.sh,
    anaconda-launcher.sh) are copied verbatim from the real Azure Linux 4.0
    installer ISO and are byte-for-byte identical to (or, for the two .ks
    files, the rendered output of) the MIT-licensed source in
    microsoft/azurelinux's base/images/vm-iso-installer/ directory. See
    reference/azl-installer/README.md for the full provenance and pinned
    upstream links.

Fedora
    Packages, including GNOME 50 (shell, session, gdm, mutter, nautilus,
    and the rest of the desktop), come from the Fedora Project. Every
    package carries its own upstream license.

GNOME
    Licensed by the GNOME Project, primarily under the LGPL and GPL. See
    https://www.gnome.org/licensing/ for the full per-component breakdown.

Microsoft Edge (Canary)
    Proprietary, installed from Microsoft's own packages.microsoft.com repo
    under the Microsoft Edge license terms:
    https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/products/agreements/microsoftedge

PowerShell
    MIT licensed at https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell, installed
    from Microsoft's official Linux repo. This repository carries
    assets/icons/powershell.png, copied from that project, for the
    .desktop launcher.

Visual Studio Code Insiders
    Distributed under the Microsoft Software License Terms
    (https://code.visualstudio.com/license) and installed from
    packages.microsoft.com. The Code - OSS source it builds from is MIT
    licensed at https://github.com/microsoft/vscode.

GitHub CLI
    The gh command. MIT licensed at https://github.com/cli/cli, installed
    from GitHub's own package repo (cli.github.com/packages/rpm).

GitHub Desktop
    Source is MIT licensed at https://github.com/desktop/desktop. This
    repository installs the community-maintained Linux packaging of it,
    https://github.com/shiftkey/desktop, not an official GitHub Linux
    build.

GitHub Copilot CLI
    The standalone copilot terminal agent. Proprietary, subject to
    GitHub's own Terms of Service:
    https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/github-terms/github-terms-of-service

GitHub Copilot (desktop GUI app)
    Proprietary, subject to the same GitHub Terms of Service as above.

.NET
    MIT licensed at https://github.com/dotnet/runtime and installed from
    Microsoft's official repo. This repository carries
    assets/icons/dotnet.svg, the official .NET logo from
    https://github.com/dotnet/brand, CC0-1.0 licensed (public domain
    dedication), used here as the icon for the .desktop launcher that
    reports "dotnet --info".

edit
    Microsoft's terminal text editor. MIT licensed at
    https://github.com/microsoft/edit. This repository carries
    assets/icons/edit.svg, copied from that project, for the .desktop
    launcher.

Plymouth
    GPL-2.0 licensed at https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/plymouth/plymouth.
    The custom boot theme at assets/plymouth/azurelinux/ is original to
    this repository (MIT, per the top of this file), except for
    assets/branding/AzureLinuxLogo.png, noted next.

assets/branding/AzureLinuxLogo.png
    This is Microsoft's Azure Linux penguin icon, taken from
    https://github.com/microsoft/azurelinux/blob/4.0/assets/azurelinux-logo-48.png.
    It is NOT MIT licensed and is not this project's to relicense.
    Microsoft permits use of this icon only in accordance with its
    trademark and brand guidelines, per the upstream notice at
    https://github.com/microsoft/azurelinux/blob/4.0/assets/NOTICE.md,
    which itself points to
    https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/legal/intellectualproperty/trademarks.
    It is used here solely to visually identify this project as building
    on Azure Linux; no ownership of the icon or the Azure Linux trademark
    is claimed, and this project is not sponsored, endorsed, or approved
    by Microsoft.

